    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework satisfies all 13 V&V 40 credibility factors at or above required levels for 12 of 13 factors. The Test conditions factor achieved level 2 against a required level of 3; however, the assessment team determined that the single quasi-static loading condition is consistent with the ASTM F1717 standard protocol and that the medium model influence and medium decision consequence together support an overall Medium assurance level determination. The output comparison results (E/uval < 1.96 and <10% difference for all QoIs) confirm model predictive adequacy within the validated domain. The package is accepted for regulatory submission.",
